      "content": "that's a good start. i want to make sure the paper addresses the counterarguments so it's harder for my professor to tear it apart. people usually bring up things like meritocracy or how redistribution might hurt economic growth—how should i frame those opposing views so they don't weaken my main point? i want to show that those arguments are basically outdated or just don't account for the systemic issues i'm talking about.",
